The problem requires finding \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\), where \(Y_1 < Y_2 < \cdots < Y_8\) are the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\). This means \(P(X < 27.3) = 0.7\) for any single observation \(X\).

The event \(Y_7 < 27.3\) is equivalent to at least seven observations being less than 27.3. Let \(S\) be the number of observations less than 27.3, which follows a binomial distribution with parameters \(n = 8\) and \(p = 0.7\). Thus,
\[
P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(S \geq 7) = P(S = 7) + P(S = 8).
\]

Calculate each probability:
\[
P(S = 7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3)^1 = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3,
\]
\[
