The integral \(\int_{0}^{1} x^3 (1 - x)^6  dx\) is evaluated using the beta function, \(B(4, 7) = \frac{\Gamma(4) \Gamma(7)}{\Gamma(11)}\). For integer values, \(\Gamma(n) = (n-1)!\), so:
- \(\Gamma(4) = 3! = 6\)
- \(\Gamma(7) = 6! = 720\)
- \(\Gamma(11) = 10! = 3,628,800\)

