* RESPONSE 1 *
**************
The solution involves finding the number of red balls in the second urn, denoted as \( r \). After setting up the equation for the probability of drawing two balls of the same color and solving, the value of \( r \) is found to be 11. This is verified by substituting \( r = 11 \) back into the probability equation, confirming it matches the given probability of \( \frac{151}{300} \).

The final answer is 11, as it represents the number of red balls in the second urn.

