Solution: The energy required to compress three carbon-carbon single bonds and stretch three carbon-carbon double bonds to the benzene bond length of 1.397 Å is calculated using the harmonic oscillator potential energy formula \( E = \frac{1}{2} k (\Delta x)^2 \), where \( k \) is the force constant and \( \Delta x \) is the displacement from the equilibrium bond length.

